    "content": "<strong>God&apos;s Plan for Israel&apos;s Land</strong>&mdash;Through disobedience to God Adam and Eve had lost Eden, and because of sin the whole earth was cursed. But if God&apos;s people followed His instruction, their land would be restored to fertility and beauty. God Himself gave them directions in regard to the culture of the soil, and they were to co-operate with Him in its restoration. Thus the whole land, under <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"144\"></span> God&apos;s control, would become an object lesson of spiritual truth. As in obedience to His natural laws the earth should produce its treasures, so in obedience to His moral law the hearts of the people were to reflect the attributes of His character.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">9<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"COL 289.1\" data-link=\"15.1251\">Christ&apos;s Object Lessons, 289</span>.</span></a></sup>",
